            </form>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
                        
                        <p>“Both sides should negotiate and come to an understanding as opposed to arguing about it,” she said.</p>
<p>Even with all the controversy, Muslims at Duke celebrated Eid al-Fitr by gathering Friday with fellow Muslims from the Triangle at the Exposition Center at the North Carolina State Fairgrounds in Raleigh.</p>
<p>“This is pretty much like Muslim Christmas,” Antepli said of the holiday. “This reflects our joy and happiness at ending Ramadan successfully, working on our spiritual muscles for the last whole month and feeling good about ourselves and our relationship with God Almighty.”</p>

